## 5. KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

### 5.1 Part A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

> **Q1. [KTU University Exam — Dec 2023]**
> **Define Node.js. Explain the role of the V8 engine in Node.js.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

Node.js is an **open-source, cross-platform, server-side JavaScript runtime environment** that executes JavaScript code outside a web browser. It is built on **Google Chrome's V8 engine** and uses an **event-driven, non-blocking I/O model**.

**Role of the V8 Engine:**
1. V8 is a **high-performance JavaScript engine** written in C++ that compiles JavaScript directly into **machine code** using **JIT (Just-In-Time) compilation**.
2. It **executes the JavaScript code** in the Node.js application layer.
3. It handles **memory allocation** and **garbage collection** for the JS runtime.
4. V8 makes Node.js **extremely fast** compared to interpreters that read code line-by-line.

> **Q2. [KTU University Exam — June 2024]**
> **List any three features of Express.js. What is middleware in Express?**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**

**Three features of Express.js:**
1. **Robust routing** mechanism for handling HTTP requests based on URL and method.
2. **Middleware support** for handling request/response processing in a chain.
3. **Fast and minimalist** — built on top of Node's `http` module with very low overhead.

**Middleware in Express:**
A **middleware function** is a function that has access to the `req` (request) object, the `res` (response) object, and the `next()` function. Middleware functions can execute code, modify `req`/`res`, end the request-response cycle, or pass control to the next middleware via `next()`.

Example: `app.use(express.json())` parses incoming JSON request bodies.

