### 5.3 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

> **⚡ Rapid Revision Checklist — Node.js Architecture, Working, and Express**

#### 🔹 Architecture
- [ ] Node.js is a **runtime environment**, not a language.
- [ ] Built on **Google Chrome's V8 JavaScript Engine**.
- [ ] **libuv** provides the **event loop**, **thread pool** (default size **4**), and **async I/O**.
- [ ] Node.js is **single-threaded** for the event loop but uses a thread pool for blocking I/O.
- [ ] The event loop has **6 phases**: Timers → Pending Callbacks → Idle/Prepare → **Poll** → Check → Close Callbacks.
- [ ] **Microtasks** (Promises, `process.nextTick()`) execute **between every phase**.
- [ ] `process.nextTick()` has the **highest priority** over all other async operations.

#### 🔹 Working with Node.js
- [ ] Node.js files use `.js` extension and are run with `node filename.js`.
- [ ] The `http` module is used to create servers; `fs` for file I/O; `path` for path operations.
- [ ] **`module.exports`** exports from a file; **`require()`** imports from a file.
- [ ] Node.js supports both **CommonJS** (`require`) and **ES Modules** (`import`).
- [ ] **NPM** is the default package manager; `package.json` tracks dependencies.
- [ ] Global objects: `global`, `__dirname`, `__filename`, `process`, `Buffer`, `module`, `exports`.

#### 🔹 Express.js
- [ ] Express is a **minimal, fast web framework** on top of Node's `http` module.
- [ ] Install with `npm install express`.
- [ ] **Routes** are defined with `app.METHOD(path, handler)`.
- [ ] HTTP methods: `GET`, `POST`, `PUT`, `DELETE`, `PATCH`.
- [ ] **Middleware** functions have access to `(req, res, next)`.
- [ ] Order of middleware **matters** — they execute in the sequence they are defined.
- [ ] Use `express.json()` and `express.urlencoded()` to parse request bodies.
- [ ] Use `express.static('folder')` to serve static files.
- [ ] **Route parameters**: `req.params.id` (from `/users/:id`).
- [ ] **Query strings**: `req.query.q` (from `/search?q=node`).
- [ ] **Error-handling middleware** must have **4 parameters**: `(err, req, res, next)`.
- [ ] Use `express.Router()` for **modular routing**.
- [ ] Status codes: `200` (OK), `201` (Created), `204` (No Content), `400` (Bad Request), `404` (Not Found), `500` (Server Error).

#### 🔹 Quick Comparison
- [ ] `app.use(path, mw)` runs for **all HTTP methods**.
- [ ] `app.get(path, handler)` runs **only for GET**.
- [ ] `res.send()` sends any type; `res.json()` sends JSON with proper Content-Type.
- [ ] `res.end()` ends the response without sending data.

